impact dimensions.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Executive Summary\\n\\nThis PR makes a targeted, minimal fix to the `scoreRe` regex in `.github/workflows/evals.yml`, extending score extraction from PR comments to cover both `Tool name trajectory` and `Response agent eval` failure message formats. The change is exactly 1 line (old regex replaced with a union using a non-capturing group), technically correct, and does not introduce any regressions. The only finding is a pre-existing, out-of-scope fragility in how scores are correlated to test names by index. No CRITICAL, HIGH, or MEDIUM issues were identified.\\n\\n**Overall Verdict**: APPROVE\\n\\n**Auto-fix Candidates**: 0 (no CRITICAL or HIGH issues)\\n**Manual Review Needed**: 0 (the 1 LOW finding is pre-existing and out of scope)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Statistics\\n\\n| Agent | CRITICAL | HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW | Total |\\n|-------|----------|------|--------|-----|-------|\\n| Code Review | 0 | 0 | 0 | 1 | 1 |\\n| Error Handling | — | — | — | — | (no artifact) |\\n| Test Coverage | — | — | — | — | (no artifact) |\\n| Comment Quality | — | — | — | — | (no artifact) |\\n| Docs Impact | — | — | — | — | (no artifact) |\\n| **Total** | **0** | **0** | **0** | **1** | **1** |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## CRITICAL Issues (Must Fix)\\n\\n_None._\\n\\n---\\n\\n## HIGH Issues (Should Fix)\\n\\n_None._\\n\\n---\\n\\n## MEDIUM Issues (Consider)\\n\\n_None._\\n\\n---\\n\\n## LOW Issues (For Consideration)\\n\\n| Issue | Location | Agent | Suggestion |\\n|-------|----------|-------|------------|\\n| Index-based score↔name correlation is fragile (pre-existing) | `.github/workflows/evals.yml:93-97` | code-review | Future bead: use a combined regex that captures test name + score from the same failure block to avoid index drift |\\n\\n### Detail: Index-based score↔name correlation (pre-existing)\\n\\n**Problem**: `scoreMap` is built by correlating `failedNames[]` to score matches by array index (`si`). If a test fails without emitting a numeric score line (e.g. `test_context_agent`, which validates JSON structure), it still occupies a slot in `failedNames[]` but produces no score match — causing any subsequent score-bearing failure to be mapped to the wrong test name.\\n\\n**Status**: Pre-existing issue, **explicitly out of scope** for this PR. The current change does not worsen it.\\n\\n**Future fix options**:\\n- Option A: Use a single combined regex that matches `FAILED ...::name` followed by the score line within a few lines (multiline match).\\n- Option B: Emit structured JSON from pytest and parse that instead of scraping text output.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Positive Observations\\n\\n- **Minimal diff**: exactly 1 line changed — no scope creep.\\n- **Non-capturing group used correctly**: `(?:...)` preserves `sm[1]` as the score capture group without disturbing group numbering.\\n- **Union regex is unambiguous**: both alternatives share the same ` score ([\\\\d.]+) below threshold` suffix.\\n- **`/g` flag + `.exec()` loop**: correct and idiomatic JS pattern for extracting multiple matches.\\n- **YAML validity**: change is inside a `github-script` `script:` key, not a shell `run:` block — no escaping concerns.\\n- **CLAUDE.md compliance**: PR body contains `Fixes #252`; no backend/frontend/database/screenshot rules apply.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Suggested Follow-up Issues\\n\\n| Issue Title | Priority | Related Finding |\\n|-------------|----------|-----------------|\\n| \\\"Improve eval score↔test name correlation in evals.yml to avoid index drift\\\" | P3 | LOW finding #1 |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Next Steps\\n\\n1. No auto-fixes needed — no CRITICAL or HIGH issues found.\\n2. PR is ready to merge (pending CI green + draft → ready conversion).\\n3. Consider creating a follow-up issue for the index-drift fragility.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Agent Artifacts\\n\\n| Agent | Artifact | Findings |\\n|-------|----------|----------|\\n| Code Review | `code-review-findings.md` | 1 |\\n| Error Handling | `error-handling-findings.md` | (not produced) |\\n| 